{
  "stem": "9168.5",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And it really made me think very hard about the decorum that has to be kept in the courtroom, and what the judge had to do.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I do not know, and I never knew, whether he really had to serve the entire 90 days.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But-- and I didn't see a weapon.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But later I learned from an American military police officer that he actually had a dagger in his hand.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So after that period of time, then security on entering the courtroom, by witnesses or the public, was greatly tightened, because witnesses would not have had a top security pass.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They would have had admittance by request from an attorney for their testimony.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I don't know the details of that kind of security that was required for them.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Then the next experiment was epidemic jaundice, conducted from 1943 to '45 at Sachsenhausen and Natzweiler.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And these were Polish Jews who were deliberately infected with epidemic jaundice, resulting in many deaths.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The ninth experiment was sterilization, conducted from 1941 to 1945-- one of the longest periods of time for experiments-- at Auschwitz and Ravensbrueck on Russian prisoners of war and Polish Jews, to develop a suitable method for the sterilization of large population growth groups by radiation, drugs, and surgery, in a planned mass genocide.",
      "word_count": 54
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "This resulted in horrible physical and mental pain and anguish.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And this was one of the experiments that was brought out in the movie, with Spencer Tracy.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The tenth experiment was typhus, conducted from 1941 to '45-- a long period of time-- at Buchenwald and Natzweiler to determine the effectiveness of vaccines.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "These victims became raving mad, suffered delirium, and 90% died a slow and frightful death.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "These were not only German criminals taken from their prisons, but Poles, Russians, and Frenchmen as well.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
